description:
&lt;p&gt;Bank partners are looking forenthusiastic, dynamic andmotivated Band 6 Anaesthetics and ODP&#39;sto join the Operating Department at Whittington Health Trust. We are ranked as ‘Outstanding’ for caring by the Care Quality Commission. If you are looking for flexible work that can fit around your other commitments this could be just what you are looking for!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Bank Anaesthetics Practitioner/ ODP , you are invaluable to us. You will be able to demonstrate a desire to work as part of a team, to develop skills in new and innovative procedures, and be competent in basic IT applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a range of services such as pre-operative assessment, Anaesthesia for inpatient and day surgery, Obstetric anaesthesia and analgesia, acute and chronic pain services and critical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank Nurses are invaluable to us and in return for their dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority of shifts over an agency worker, accommodating your availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designated onsite Business Partners to offer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated recruitment team to ensure you can work as quickly as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated compliance team that ensures you remain compliant to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core skills training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bookings team to ensure you work when and wherever you want to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this role please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
